5347 
5353 /******************************************************************************/
5354 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F0xx device product */
5355 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
5356 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
5357 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
5358 /* product lines within the same STM32F0 Family */
5359 /******************************************************************************/
5360 
5361 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
5362 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQn ADC1_IRQn
5363 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQn DMA1_Channel1_IRQn
5364 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQn DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQn
5365 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
5366 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
5367 #define RCC_CRS_IRQn RCC_IRQn
5368 #define TIM6_DAC_IRQn TIM6_IRQn
5369 
5370 
5371 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
5372 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQHandler ADC1_IRQHandler
5373 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel1_IRQHandler
5374 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQHandler
5375 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
5376 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
5377 #define RCC_CRS_IRQHandler RCC_IRQHandler
5378 #define TIM6_DAC_IRQHandler TIM6_IRQHandler
5379 
5380 
5381 #ifdef __cplusplus
5382 }
5383 #endif /* __cplusplus */
5384 
5385 #endif /* STM32F030x8_H */
